Documentation

output: github_document

Online documentation for my R packages. Click on the names for links to the full documentation. All packages are available from CRAN unless otherwise indicated.

Packages:

hansard

An ironically named R package to automatically fetch data from the UK Parliament API. Available on CRAN and GitHub.

cqcr

Get data from the Care Quality Commission API. Available on GitHub

mnis

An R package for downloading data from the Members’ Names Information Service API operated by the UK Parliament.

parlitools

A collection of tools, datasets and maps for analysing UK politics.

nomisr

nomisr is for accessing Nomis data – UK labour market statistics, census data and other population data – with R. Part of the rOpenSci community.

fixerapi

fixerapi is an R client for the fixer.io currency exchange rate API.

refuge

refuge is an R client for the Refuge Restrooms API, which records public restrooms that are friendly to trans and non-binary people.

guardianapi

Access to the Guardian open data platorm API, containing all articles published in the Guardian from 1999 to the present.

ukpolice

Access to the UK Police API, with data on police forces, reported crimes and the use of stop and search.

emisc

emisc is a collection of miscellaneous functions that I have made that may or may not be useful, and that may or may not duplicate existing work.

emisc is currently not available on CRAN. You can install emisc from github with:

# install.packages("devtools")
devtools::install_github("evanodell/emisc")
